{{Youmay|the [[Star Wars Legends|Legends]] organization responsible for various weather conditions on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]|[[Coruscant weather control]], the system that manipulated weather on [[Coruscant]] in the [[canon]] continuity}}
The '''Coruscant WeatherNet''', also known as the '''Coruscant Weather Control Network''' and '''Coruscant climate control''', was responsible for various weather conditions on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]. During an accident involving a [[Waste Canister Delivery Port 84-D-21|waste container]] spill and aerial dispersal, the WeatherNet canceled prevailing winds for that day.

The WeatherNet's control of the [[Coruscanti/Legends|Coruscanti]] climate even extended to the timing of the seasons. In one instance, it responded to a request by the [[Planet/Legends|planet's]] [[Wildlife Commission]] to begin summer early in hopes of extending the mating season of Coruscant's native [[Hawk-bat/Legends|hawk-bat]] and increasing the [[Species/Legends|species]]' population.<ref name="Hnn-Less Hawk-bats Means Early Summer">{{HoloNetNewsWeb|45|life/13228_3.html|Less Hawk-bats Means Early Summer}}</ref>

During the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]], much of WeatherNet's infrastructure was lost, though it most likely was rebuilt in the decades that followed.

==Behind the scenes==
''[[Coruscant and the Core Worlds]]'' states that one of the instructions for the WeatherNet is "The rain may never fall until after sundown, and by eight the morning fog must disappear", concluding "the government said that's how conditions are on Coruscant." These are all lyrics, or paraphrased lyrics, from the title song of the musical [[Wikipedia:Camelot (musical)|''Camelot'']].

